{{merge to|CECAFA Cup|discuss=Talk:CECAFA Cup#Merger proposal|date=September 2018}} {{Infobox international football competition | tourney_name = CECAFA Cup | year = 2016 | other_titles = CECAFA Senior Challenge Cup | image = | size = | alt = | caption = | country = | dates = | num_teams = | sub-confederations = | venues = | cities = | champion = | count = | second = | third = | fourth = | matches = | goals = | attendance = | top_scorer = | goalkeeper = | prevseason = [[2015 CECAFA Cup|2015]] | nextseason = [[2017 CECAFA Cup|2017]] | updated = }}
The '''2016 CECAFA Cup''' was to be the 39th edition of the annual [[CECAFA Cup]], an international football competition consisting of the national teams of member nations of the [[Council for East and Central Africa Football Associations]] (CECAFA). In September 2016, it was confirmed that Kenya would host the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37310529|title=Kenya step in to host Cecafa events|publisher=BBC Sport|date=9 September 2016}}</ref> Originally, it was to be hosted in Sudan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/35232983|title=Sudan named as 2016 Cecafa Cup hosts|work=BBC Sport|date=5 January 2015|accessdate=8 January 2015}}</ref>
In November 2016, Kenya announced they are not ready to host the tournament and CECAFA officials are looking to persuade Sudan to take over as hosts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newtimes.co.rw/section/article/2016-11-05/205055/|title=CECAFA looking for Cup hosts after Kenya withdrawals|work=New Times Rwanda|date=5 November 2016|accessdate=25 November 2016}}</ref>
In December 2016, CECAFA announced the 2016 edition of the tournament will be canceled.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/38265595|title=Cecafa 2016 tournaments cancelled|publisher=BBC Sport|date=9 December 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref>
