'''Cuba Nostalgia''' is an annual 3-day festival in [[Little Havana]], a neighbourhood in [[Miami]], [[Florida]], where [[Cuban-Americans]] celebrate Cuba before it was taken over by the [[Fidel Castro|Castro]] regime.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2002/06/16/us/longing-for-the-old-cuba-stirs-a-boom-in-nostalgia.html|title=Longing for the Old Cuba Stirs a Boom in Nostalgia|date=16 June 2002|work=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=15 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cubanet.org/CNews/y00/may00/22e2.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-05-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120320022418/http://www.cubanet.org/CNews/y00/may00/22e2.htm |archivedate=2012-03-20 |df= }}</ref> The festival has also hosted a database to reconnect those who escaped from Cuba as children during [[Operation Peter Pan]].<ref>http://www.miamiherald.com/2009/05/17/1053424/cubans-reconnect-with-past-through.html</ref>
