==Scoreboard==
The EBU and [[PricewaterhouseCoopers|PwC audit company]] checked and verified the individual jury and televoting results, which were combined to create the overall national vote for the contests.  On 18 June 2012, the EBU published the following results.<ref name="Split results out">{{cite web|url=http://www.esctoday.com/?p=36768|title=Split Jury and Televoting results announced|publisher=ESCToday.com|last=Hondal|first=Victor|date=18 June 2012|accessdate=18 June 2012}}</ref><ref name="Split jury-televote">{{cite web|url=http://www.eurovision.tv/page/news?id=eurovision_2012_split_jury-televote_results_revealed|title=Eurovision 2012 split jury-televote results revealed|publisher=[[European Broadcasting Union]]|last=Siim|first=Jarmo|date=18 June 2012|accessdate=18 June 2012}}</ref>

